static Document de.unibi.techfak.bibiserv.biodom.AbstractBioDOM.transform (  final String  NS1,
final String  NS2,
final Document  doc
)  throws StylesheetNotAvailableException, NSNotSupportedException, TransformerConfigurationException, TransformerException, BioDOMException [static]
 

Transform the given document from XML namespace NS1 to namespace NS2 and returns the translated document. A StylesheetNotAvailableExpception is thrown if no suitable XSLT stylesheet is available in current release.

Transform uses the BioDOM.properties.xml (found in the config subdir) to get the shortcut names of the XML namespace identifier. The shortcuts of the namespoces are used to build the file name of the suitable XSLT stylesheet. A XSLT stylesheet should be stored in the resources/xsl subfolder using the following style : 'shortcut1 of NS1' + '_' + 'to' + '_' + 'shortcut of NS2' + '.xsl'
The following table is a (uncompleted) list of available stylesheet which comes with current release of BioDOM

FROMTOREMARK
http://hobit.sourceforge.net/20060201/rnastructML http://hobit.sourceforge.net/20060201/sequenceML extract all sequence information from RNAstructML and store the information in a SequenceML document
http://hobit.sourceforge.net/20060515/rnastructAlignmentML http:///hobit.sourceforge.net/20060201/sequenceML extract all sequence information from RNAStructAlignmentML and store the information in a SequenceML document
http://hobit.sourceforge.net/20060505/sequenceAnnotationML http:///hobit.sourceforge.net/20060201/sequenceML extract all sequence information from sequenceAnnotationML and store the information in a SequenceML document

Parameters:
NS1 - A String describing a XML namespace converting from, e.g. http://hobit.sourceforge.net/xsds/20060201/rnastructML
NS2 - A String describing a XMl namespace converting to, e.g. http://hobit.sourceforge.net/xsds/20060201/sequenceML
doc - input document
Returns:
Returns the translated document
Exceptions:
StylesheetNotAvailableException,if no suitable XSLT stylesheet is found
NSNotSupportedException,if no suitable NS is found in properties
TransformerConfigurationException,if the Transformer can't be configured or no Transformer is found
TransformerException,if transformation fails
BioDOMException,if BioDOM properties can't be loaded
